cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.ST

This paper discusses regularization techniques in the context of neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of regularization to improve generalization performance in the presence of noise, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of regularization in the context of image processing (cs.CV) and the analysis of coefficients (cs.ST), which further supports these sub-categories as likely options.
